---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Corbin Riches, an Engineering Physics student interested in photonics, cryogenics, simulation, and technical writing."
>
	<section class="page-header">
		<p class="eyebrow">about</p>
		<h1>Engineering Physics, with a bias toward useful systems.</h1>
		<p>
			I am an Engineering Physics student interested in the places where theory, hardware,
			and computation start talking to each other.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section two-column">
		<div>
			<h2>Focus Areas</h2>
			<p>
				My current interests include photonics, quantum dots, cryogenics, detector systems,
				scientific computing, and simulation. I like problems where the math matters, the
				measurements are real, and the final explanation has to be clear enough to use.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="terminal-card">
			<p><span>&gt;</span> photonics and semiconductor devices</p>
			<p><span>&gt;</span> low-temperature systems</p>
			<p><span>&gt;</span> numerical modeling and visualization</p>
			<p><span>&gt;</span> technical writing and documentation</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>What This Site Is For</h2>
		<p>
			This is a place to collect project writeups, notes, reading, and contact information
			without making the whole thing heavier than it needs to be. The goal is a readable
			digital portfolio that can grow as the work gets more specific.
		</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
